g) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform-style:preserve-3d" class="accordion-icon"></div></div><nav style="height:0px" class="accordion-list w-dropdown-list"><p class="accordion-list-content">A pergola is an open-air structure featuring vertical posts and crossbeams that provide partial shade and architectural appeal. It enhances outdoor living by creating a defined space for relaxation, dining, or entertaining while still allowing light and airflow. Pergolas can serve as a beautiful extension of patios, gardens, or poolside areas. Many homeowners use them as focal points, adding style and character to their backyard. They also provide a framework for climbing plants, string lights, or drapery. By blending beauty with function, pergolas elevate outdoor spaces.</p></nav></div><div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="0278690b-a854-b087-3ccd-c1a6e4cfb0c7" style="opacity:0" class="accordion-item w-dropdown"><div class="accordion-toggle w-dropdown-toggle"><h4 style="color:rgb(255,255,255)" class="accordion-title">What materials are commonly used to build pergolas?</h4><div style="color:rgb(255,255,255);-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform-style:preserve-3d" class="accordion-icon"></div></div><nav style="height:0px" class="accordion-list w-dropdown-list"><p class="accordion-list-content">Pergolas are most commonly built with aluminum, wood, or vinyl. Aluminum pergolas are lightweight, rust-resistant, and require minimal maintenance, making them a long-lasting option. Wood offers a classic, natural look but requires staining or sealing to prevent weather damage. Vinyl provides a low-maintenance alternative that resists rot and fading. Aluminum is increasingly popular because it combines strength with durability, especially in climates with heavy rain or sun exposure. Each material provides distinct benefits.</p></nav></div><div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="0278690b-a854-b087-3ccd-c1a6e4cfb0d0" style="opacity:0" class="accordion-item w-dropdown"><div class="accordion-toggle w-dropdown-toggle"><h4 style="color:rgb(255,255,255)" class="accordion-title">Can a pergola provide full shade or weather protection?</h4><div style="color:rgb(255,255,255);-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform-style:preserve-3d" class="accordion-icon"></div></div><nav style="height:0px" class="accordion-list w-dropdown-list"><p class="accordion-list-content">By design, traditional pergolas offer partial shade with their open roof beams. However, they can be upgraded with features such as retractable canopies, louvers, or polycarbonate panels to provide more coverage. Motorized louvered systems allow homeowners to adjust sunlight and airflow as needed. For rain protection, insulated roof panels or waterproof covers can be added. These enhancements transform pergolas into versatile structures that provide comfort in different weather conditions. Customization ensures the desired balance of light and shade.</p></nav></div><div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="0278690b-a854-b087-3ccd-c1a6e4cfb0d9" style="opacity:0" class="accordion-item last-faq w-dropdown"><div class="accordion-toggle w-dropdown-toggle"><h4 style="color:rgb(255,255,255)" class="accordion-title">Are pergolas customizable to match my home’s design?</h4><div style="color:rgb(255,255,255);-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(null) rotateY(null) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform-style:preserve-3d" class="accordion-icon"></div></div><nav style="height:0px" class="accordion-list w-dropdown-list"><p class="accordion-list-content">Yes, pergolas are highly customizable in size, style, and finish. Homeowners can choose modern, minimalist designs or classic, decorative styles depending on preferences. Options include different frame colors, roof designs, and integrated features such as lighting, fans, or privacy screens. Pergolas can be freestanding in a garden or attached to the home for a seamless transition from indoor to outdoor space. With endless customization options, each pergola can be designed to complement architecture and enhance outdoor living.</p></nav></div></div></div></div></div><section class="uui-section_layout75"><div class="uui-page-padding-7"><div class="uui-container-large-7"><div class="uui-padding-vertical-xhuge-8"><div class="uui-layout75_component"><div class="uui-text-align-center"><div class="uui-max-width-large-3"><div class="uui-button-row-7 button-row-center"><div class="uui-badge-2 is-primary"><div class="text-block-12">Locations</div></div></div><div class="uui-space-xsmall-5"></div><h2 class="uui-heading-medium-6">We Also Provide Our Services in These Locations</h2><div class="uui-space-xsmall-5"></div><div class="uui-text-size-large-6">We proudly serve homeowners across Florida, offering top-notch craftsmanshi